  "text": "We now consider a path planning problem, similar to the one presented in [CITATION_1] : an agent wants to exit a 4 × 21 maze [shown in Fig. 6(a) ] using the least possible time. Starting from the upper-left corner, the agent can move up, down, left and right, but can only exit the grid at the lower-right corner. Here, a white box stands for a normal place where the agent needs one time unit to pass through. A shaded box represents a \"shaky\" place: if an agent reaches a \"shaky\" place, then he may risk jumping to the starting point (\"reboot\"). The true transition probability of the jump follows a distribution",
